                                    <strong>Behavioral Health Services: </strong>Screening for mental health conditions, counseling, and referrals for therapy or psychiatric services.
                                </p>
                                <p class="profile-position">
                                    <strong>Women's Health Services: </strong>Preventive care for women including Pap smears, mammograms, pelvic exams, and counseling on family planning.
                                </p>
                                <p class="profile-position">
                                    <strong>Men's Health Services:  </strong>Preventive screenings and counseling tailored to men's health issues such as prostate health and erectile dysfunction.
                                </p>
                                <p class="profile-position">
                                    <strong>Nutrition Counseling: </strong> Guidance on healthy eating habits, weight management, and dietary modifications to prevent and manage chronic conditions.
                                </p>
                                <p class="profile-position">
                                    <strong>Smoking Cessation Programs: </strong>Support and resources for individuals looking to quit smoking or using tobacco products.
                                </p>
                                <p class="profile-position">
                                    <strong>Physical Activity Programs: </strong>Recommendations and resources for physical activity, exercise routines, and fitness assessments to promote overall health.
                                </p>
                                <p class="profile-position">
                                    <strong>Chronic Disease Management: </strong>Monitoring and management of chronic conditions like diabetes, hypertension, asthma, and others to prevent complications.
                                </p>
                                <p class="profile-position">
                                    <strong>Genetic Counseling: </strong>Counseling and testing for individuals with a family history of genetic disorders or hereditary conditions.
                                </p
                                <p class="profile-position">
                                    <strong>Travel Health Services: </strong>Vaccinations, medications, and education for travelers to prevent travel-related illnesses.
                                </p>
                                <p class="profile-position">
                                    <strong>Occupational Health Services: </strong>Services for employees to promote workplace health and safety and prevent occupational injuries and illnesses.
                                </p>
                                <p class="profile-position">
                                    <strong>Telemedicine for Preventive Care: </strong>Remote consultations and follow-ups to provide preventive healthcare services to individuals who cannot visit the hospital in person.
